<p>Commonwealth of Australia<br/>Department of Defence<br/>Melbourne<br/>4th July 1916</p>
<p>No 58002</p>
<p>Dear Judge Ferguson</p>
<p>General Ramaciotti has already conveyed to you my sympathy in your sad loss, but I would like to personally express my sincere regret and sympathy with you in your trouble.</p>
<p>Apart from my personal interest, I am informed by my officers that your son was regarded as a highly qualified and competent officer whose advancement in the Forces was assured.</p>
<p>Yours faithfully,</p>
<p>G.F. Pearce</p>
<p>His Honor<br/>Mr. Justice Ferguson<br/>Supreme Court<br/>Sydney, N.S.W.</p>
